name: Rebecca
text: What a lovely restaurant. It is so rare to have options for indulgent vegan food AND whole food plant based meals in the same spot that are both well thought out, complex and delicious. We tried the Harvest Bowl (WFPB) and the Garbage Plate (the opposite of WFPB) and they were both delicious. Desserts were half-off on Sunday. Not sure if that is typical but it was nice. Very cute spot. Definitely stop in if you are in the area. Note: there are no public restrooms.
title: Veg.Edible

name: Lois Schreur
text: This is my go-to place whenever I don't want to cook for myself and my go-to place whenever I need cookies or cake for a family event.  Some of my favorites are the tomato soup, the potato soup, and the garbage plate--pure comfort food.
title: Veg.Edible

name: Doki Wolfe
text:
It was the Scorpio New Moon of Samhain, 2k24,
When I had an exhausting Halloween
And dozed early the night before.
I slept more than 8 hours, woke at 4,
And stayed up 4 more,
And lied in pain
For half the day
With no energy to remain
I've earned a treat
Just to feel safe
So I sought value in a trade
I can barely move,
I can barely stand,
I'd be grateful for some
strength in my hands. 
Since time isn't real
It wasn't long before
I received a text
That they were at my door
They asked me how I was
I said I'm better now
They wished me a good one
And I ran back into my house
There's a blessing on my shake,
And a heart on the box
Someone loved me today
And added two cookies on top.
title: Veg.Edible

name: Carly Barth
responseFromOwnerText: Hi! Thank you so so much for leaving this heart warming review! Happy to help walk through the menu so you and your husband can enjoy a delicious, safe meal and dessert. Can’t wait to see you back in the shop
text: We had a lovely, deliciously crafted meal the other night! My husband is on a very restrictive low fodmap only, gluten free, dairy-free diet and has not eaten out in two years. Matt and Stacie were able to accommodate every single one of his customizations. They didn’t blink an eye when we stood there researching specific ingredients to make sure it was safe to eat. Stacie even went as far to research baked good options while we ate and there were two he was able to enjoy. That’s a big deal as he hasn’t be able to eat a baked good in two years! It was an excellent experience and we definitely will be back!
title: Veg.Edible

name: JM Yodafriend

text: I visited Veg.Edible with some friends who have special dietary needs. All I had was the lava cake, so I can't comment on any of the other food ... but the lava cake, and its accompanying ice cream, was surprisingly good! I've never eaten vegan / gluten free before and I wasn't sure what to expect, but I think I would recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for those specialities.  Limited seating, but the tables and benches were clean and comfortable enough. Some additional dessert options (pie? other cakes?) would be nice to see

responseFromOwnerText:
Hi! Thanks for this feedback. The v/gf bun is toasted and all the sauces come on the side. Our burgers start at $15 and it is $2 to add cheese. While we very much love Benson Brewery, they don’t have a gluten-free bun or vegan cheese, and can’t accommodate for allergens like we do in our dedicated space. In comparison to our friends around the corner at Barchen, their vegan burger on a non-gluten free bun with cheese is $16. 

Our prices are on par with the high quality ingredients we source that allow us to craft a safe space for those with allergies and dietary restrictions.
text: I was happy to find another vegan option in Benson. But why is the bun so dry. The cheese was like plastic and the beyond burger was dryer than the Sahara.  $17 dollars is far too much for such a low quality burger. Benson Brewery was way better vegan options for the price. The lady at the counter was pleasant but didn't make up for the quality of the food.

name: Adelaide Opitz
responseFromOwnerText: Thank you for the 5-stars, Ade! We appreciate you and Dustin so so much. S’mores bars will be making a regular appearance in the pastry case
text:
Veg.Edible is nothing short of a culinary haven, especially for those navigating dietary restrictions or allergies.

What sets Veg.Edible apart is their unwavering commitment to providing dishes free from animal products, gluten, and nuts. In a city where options for those with dairy and gluten restrictions are disappointingly scarce, Veg.Edible emerges as a game-changer. It's heartening to see a restaurant not only address these dietary needs but also excel in delivering flavorsome meals that resonate with passion and purpose.

The chefs at Veg.Edible are nothing short of culinary artists. Their intentionality shines through each dish, showcasing a deep-seated passion for creating food that everyone can relish. And speaking of delights, their baked goods are a revelation! Every bite of their bakery items leaves me in awe; doing this without the use of any gluten products is an incredible feat! It's a testament to their culinary prowess. Location-wise, their spot in Benson is a boon for those in the midtown area like myself. Its convenience ensures that my visits are frequent, and each time, I leave with a heart full of gratitude and a belly full of deliciousness.

If you are seeking a dining destination that celebrates diversity, flavor, and inclusivity, look no further. Veg.Edible has not only filled a gap but has done so with unparalleled finesse. Highly, highly recommended!
title: Veg.Edible

text:
Veg.Edible's baking is NO JOKE. Stop at Veg.Edible if you are in Omaha and in need of a vegan/gluten free cake or baked good. They are incredible, and what a delight it is to find GF baking that feels like the "real" thing!

I am so thrilled to have Veg.Edible brick and mortar in the heart of Benson. It's a perfect fit for the neighborhood. We always need more restaurants catering specifically TO dietary restrictions, and Veg.Edible's all vegan, all gluten free menu does not disappoint. You know that you're getting a safe dish every time, and damn, the dishes are good, too. Cholesterol-free, guilt-free, dairy-free deliciousness. Their dinner menu is sure to have something yummy for everyone.
title: Veg.Edible

name: April Eyberg
text: We're so lucky to have Stacie and the Veg.Edible team right here in Council Bluffs.  They are the only place that offers totally vegan and gluten free food in town. title: Veg.Edible

name: Erin Wetzel
text:
Everything, and I mean everything is GF + Vegan! Everything is delicious and tastes amazing (you forget you’re eating VEGAN + GF). Mind blown!

I stumbled upon this business, composed of 1 (yes ONE) very talented lady. She not only makes stuff directly for the consumer, but also for businesses like:  Edge of the Universe Cafe, 13th Street Coffee, Omaha Tower Cafe, etc. Not to mention Pop-Ups, Featuring all kinds of amazing creations.

I looked her up online via her FB and Insta accounts,  which brought me to her website.  Stacie does pop-up food events at different locations throughout the metro, but better yet, she will make your food from scratch and deliver it. Caters, too.

She also offers pick-up options.

Her menu consists of sweet and savory Vegan + GF items: Brunch Items, Dinner, Lunch, desserts (cakes, cupcakes, brownies, scones, muffins) hush puppies w homemade vegan/GF ranch dipping sauce, on and on and on…….Come on!!!!!!

I was so overwhelmed and overjoyed by these options that I have ordered/eaten her food every week since discovering her. So much love and time goes into her food. She is dedicated + so easy to work with, plus so accommodating! How often can a GF person eat vegan “meat” options,  since many vegan chefs use Seitan as their main “meat” product. Her food is amazing!  One cannot tell that it is vegan or GF!  We have been so impressed. We did the ordering via her website, then discussed specifics via Text,  and she responds almost immediately. It is such an easy process and she is extremely punctual; exceeding our expectations!

We ordered the following GF + Vegan items and everything is full of flavor, delicious, and fairly priced: Muffins, Cupcakes, cake, decorated sugar cookies,  vegan bailey’s brownies, McRib Sand + fries, hush puppies + homemade ranch, breaded tofu fishwich + fries, buffalo mac n cheese.

Give her a try.  You will not be disappointed! I cannot wait for a future brick and mortar location.
title: Veg.Edible
